    "finalText": "I can’t give you a real “cash available today” number right now because the live Acumatica cash-position pull failed.\n\nWhat I can confirm:\n- The **ERP cash report is the source of truth** for this question.\n- That source is currently returning a **system error** on the AP/check side, so any net cash number I gave you would be guesswork.\n\nWhat’s wrong:\n- **Acumatica cash-position report failed**\n- Failure point: **AP checks fetch**\n- Result: I **cannot verify today’s available cash** from live accounting data\n\nWhat to do next:\n- **Retry the live cash report** once the Acumatica API issue clears\n- If you need an immediate operating view, I can still pull:\n  1. **AR aging** — what should be coming in  \n  2. **AP aging** — what’s owed out  \n  3. **Recent invoices and bills** — near-term cash pressure\n\nThat won’t replace bank-available cash, but it will tell you whether today’s position is likely tightening or loosening.\n\nIf you want, I’ll pull **AR aging + AP aging + recent invoices/bills** now and give you the best practical cash read despite the ERP failure."
  },
